      "message": "[Critical] Line 133: Plugin-provided bodyOverwrite is copied directly into the displayed message body without preserving the same body normalization/conversion path used for normal message bodies. If plugins can provide arbitrary data, this can bypass existing message-body handling and allow misleading/spoofed content or unexpected rich-text/control content to be rendered as if it were the sender\u0027s original message. Route the overwrite through the same validation/sanitization/conversion used for message bodies, or explicitly constrain this field before assigning it.\n```suggestion\nconst auto overwrittenBody \u003d bodyOverwriteIt.value();\n// Apply the same body normalization/sanitization policy used for msg.body before display.\nbody \u003d interaction::to_body(overwrittenBody, type);\n```",
      "revId": "dd0e0ba2baab830ec4401a08c12c78b26ddc4882",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
