      "message": "[Critical] Line 97: Adding pluginData to the serialized SwarmMessage DBus structure changes the wire signature unconditionally. Any client/daemon version skew that still sends the old structure will fail to deserialize correctly, which can break swarm loading and message updates during upgrades. Add a compatibility strategy, such as versioning the DBus type/signal, gating the new field behind an updated interface, or documenting and enforcing that client and daemon must be upgraded together.",
